For example, say a customer purchases a new TV with a warranty. Traditionally, one would have to store the paperwork and receipts very carefully and organized. However, with CT, they can upload their receipts, input all their paperwork and warranty details, and be completely up to speed with it. Anytime they have a problem with the TV, they simply log onto the website and their information is there, easily stored and categorically accessible. Furthermore, several months before your warranty is about to expire, CT will shoot the user a reminder e-mail reminding him or her about the warranty, in case any claim needs to be created. Beyond warranties, CT will also be an essential to dealing with customer service. Things like uploading the phone conversation, or making detailed notes/summaries of each phone conversation, as well as the rep's name, ID #, etc. can all be inputted and tracked directly on the site.  Together with these two services, we hope to help the business world and make the lives of businessmen and women much easier, while still be innovative.

Description: Cut Your Watts provides smart plugs & meters for customers to measure energy utilized for reducing electric bills and power wastage.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Cut Your Watts is no risk, no-money-down, satisfaction guaranteed! You pay nothing until you see a smaller electric bill! CutYourWatts sets up smart plugs (e.g. Belkin WeMo Insight) or meters for the customer. For a few days, the customer takes notes when things are turned on and off. The customer sends the notes and meter data to CutYourWatts. Energy hogs that consume power even though they are "off" are identified. The customer decides what to do with each energy hog: remove, replace, or control. The customer uses smart plugs or less expensive power strips to control the hogs. The customer gets smaller electric bills. The customer shares the savings with CutYourWatts through monthly PayPal payments. Premium customers use simulations to do what-if scenarios for greater savings.

The power of AMS VariCode is that a single complex dot coding pattern can accommodate many different coded overlays and identify many different images in one AMS VaniCode message frame. The application of this new security technology is applicable to a wide range of markets, industries, and business enterprises as detailed in Applications & Markets Business Plan on this website. Full Description: BoatBold helps you find exactly the boat you need, at precisely the moment when you need to rent it.This is a place to rent boats and reduce the expense of owning a boat by sharing it with your fellow Minnesotans.  About BoatBold Our mission is two-fold; first we want to make the boat rental process as easy and painless as possible. Secondly, we want to help boat owners have more than just two happy days. We want to make every day owning a boat as happy as the first day you bought it by turning your boat into a money maker that covers it's own expenses. BoatBold is a startup boat rental marketplace based in Rochester, Minnesota. In 2018, BoatBold founder Tim Robinson, an Air Force Veteran and RCTC Computer Science student decided to enter the Student Division of the Minnesota Cup to improve his professional and technical experience, while going to school and building a tech company in southern Minnesota.  Tim launched the BoatBold web application on May 3rd, 2018 to allow boat owners to list their boats for rent and allowing boat renters a place to easily review and compare the features of available boats. BoatBold is focused on freshwater boat rentals some of the things that differentiate us from our competitors are our focused on lake-based search for boats, focus on smaller boats and land based pickup and shipping of boat rentals. (Meaning that you can rent someone's boat, even if it is parked in their driveway on a boat trailer.) BoatBold is a big supporter of building technology companies anywhere and hopes to eventually employ more people in Southern Minnesota. Minnesota is a great place to start a boat rental startup as 15% of Minnesotan's own boats, store boats, and pay for expenses for boats, despite having one of the shortest boating seasons. At 15% boat ownership, Minnesota has the greatest boat ownership per capita in the USA. We believe this makes it a unique environment to build considerable supply of boat owners on our platform and encourage boat sharing to alleviate the expenses of boat ownership while providing renters with an easy, friendly boat rental experience.  Our largest competition which is focused on renting larger boats on the coasts has only 4,000 boats on their platform, and very few in Minnesota, while the state of Minnesota boats over 813,000 boats.  BoatBold makes everyday a happy day for boat owners!
